race.comment: Most of these are struggling for winning form. DASHING DONKEY (1) was fifth in a deeper race last time and did win the start prior when raced on the speed and fought on well. Well placed this grade and gets chance to bounce back. PENDANTE (5) hasn't been far away at last couple of runs. Has a low draw and looks nicely placed with the claim. One of the main hopes. WHISTLER GIRL (9) led until the final stages last time over 1800m in a solid run. Expected to give a sight again. BABBLE ON (12) has not won for a long time with just one career win from 24 starts. Last start finished 5.5 lengths away in fifth over 1600m at Corowa when got well back and wound up late. Claim helps and should be running on strongly.
